We recommended that Management: 

Require the Municipal Accountant to maintain subsidiary ledgers for Due to BIR account;

Fast track the reconciliation of the unremitted taxes withheld and ensure that monthly taxes withheld were remitted intact and timely;

Require the Municipal Treasurer’s Office to remit immediately the unremitted DST of ₱ 53,650.00; and

Impose penalties for late remittances of taxes withheld against the employee/s that caused the delay.

Submit all the Supplemental Budget and ordinances pertaining to the realignment/reversion/reprogramming of funds;

Refrain from declaring the unexpended balances of MOOE as savings prior to year-end; and

Ensure that the AIP prepared is aligned with the Annual Budget.

We recommended that Management:

require the Accountable Officer (AO) to immediately settle their unliquidated cash advances;

instruct the Municipal Accountant not to grant additional cash advance unless the previous cash advances were settled and withhold the salary of the accountable officer should he/she failed to submit the liquidation report on or before January 20 of unliquidated prior years’ cash advances; 


stop the practice of resorting to cash advance in the procurement of supplies and services required during the conduct of the annual activities/events of the LGU; and

instruct the Municipal Accountant to process only liquidation reports with complete and proper supporting documents and record the same to appropriate accounts.

We recommended that Management require the Municipal Budget Office to:
adopt the account names/codes used by the Accounting Office as prescribed under PPSAS to achieve uniformity and harmony for better financial reporting;

submit supplemental budgets, realignments, augmentations for specific budget items wherein actual expenses exceeded its appropriations;

provide basis for the amounts identified as sources of augmentation and determine the exact amount allotted to Other General Services and Consultancy Services accounts; and

correctly prepare and maintain the registries of appropriation for better budget monitoring.

